----------------------------------------------------------------------
README
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This example runs a simple noise simulation (NOISE_TOMOGRAPHY = 1), using a noise source time function as in Tromp et al. (2010), Figure 2a.

To run the example simulation, just execute script:
./run_this_example.sh

You can check out the output files in the local directory OUTPUT_FILES/ and compare them to the solutions provided in REF_SEIS/.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

Tip:

* To modify the noise source time function: 

1. generate a file using a Peterson noise model, stored in file NOISE_TOMOGRAPHY/S_squared:
  ./run_generate_S_squared.sh

2. set in Par_file:
  ..
  noise_source_time_function_type = 0
  ..

3. re-run the simulation

----------------------------------------------------------------------

